10/12/2010
WASHINGTON, United States -- Secretary of State Hillary Clinton met with Albanian Foreign Minister Edmond Haxhinasto in Washington on Thursday (December 9th) , confirming the countries' strong bilateral ties.
Clinton described Albania as a very close ally of the United States and NATO, one that plays an important role in the region, especially in Kosovo.
Regional developments and the processes in Kosovo were discussed, Haxhinasto said.
(VoA, Telegrafi, Balkan Web - 09/12/10)Theme:
Regional co-operation Issue:
Albania/US relations
